abstract: >
  An autonomous AI-agent–driven cryptanalysis pipeline for the Elliptic Curve
  Discrete Logarithm Problem (ECDLP), implemented end-to-end by Anthropic's
  Claude Sonnet 4.6 / Opus 4.7 via the Claude Code interface, demonstrated on IBM
  Quantum Heron r2 hardware. Two qualitatively distinct results:
  (Phase 0, 2026-04) 22-bit (m=22) private-key recovery — six algorithmic
  steps beyond Lelli's 17-bit Q-Day Prize Round-1 winner — using
  adaptive-counting and Stern-Brocot continued-fraction lift extraction
  in the verification-filter regime; (Phase 1, 2026-05-25) 4-bit (m=3)
  recovery on ibm_kingston via cross-shot Hidden Number Problem
  (HNP) scoring + top-K verification — the first hardware ECDLP decode
  whose recovery does not rely on per-shot verification-filter brute
  force, demonstrating signal-regime recovery at the smallest non-
  trivial scale.
